The Konikit Carbon Fiber Money Clip Wallet most probably does a find job of blocking the devices that the bad guys use to steal your credit card information right out of your back pocket. I don't doubt that for a minute - but how would we know it's working anyway? That's pretty much a matter of faith on the part of the consumer.

But I do have a problem with the construction of this aluminum wallet: the weak point is definitely the black ""elastic bands"" on both sides that is designed to hold the wallet tightly closed. The bands do that right now, and they stretch nicely as more cards are inserted into the wallet. But how long are they going to do the job before the stretch out of shape or break- losing their ability to keep the wallet tightly closed (that's all that's keeping your cards in place)?

And then there's the rigid clip outside the wallet by which it can be clipped to your belt - not something i want to do in a large crowd. If I'm worried about someone stealing my data with a reader, I'm more worried about someone stealing the whole wallet right off my belt and running away with the actual cards in hand. This is the kind of wallet that should be slipped into a man's side pocket because it's small enough to do that - but with that clip, that's not going to happen. (And, yes, I do realize this is intended to be a ""money clip,"" but it is still too uncomfortable to fit inside a pocket this way...I tried it.)

Time will tell how long this holds up, so I'm giving it three stars (minus one star for the elastic and one for the uncomfortable/dangerous clip).

I haven't worn a backpack purse since the late 90s' when I was in high school. I've been a bit nostalgic seeing the youth bring them back.
I spent a week reading reviews and searching for the right size, color and price for my next backpack purse. I narrowed it down to two purses. Obviously this was one of them and the other was the LuckyZ red backpack purse. Looking at pictures and reviews and what each bag had to offer I decided to give this one a try. The other was slouchy and the straps looked cheap. The LuckyZ (the other) was more my style when it comes to looks, I like the worn in, vintage style of the bag, but the reviews on this one and the quality (based on the pictures), had more to offer for a few dollars cheaper. Plus, I planned to start carrying around my sketch pad and drawing tools, the fact that this is water proof was reason enough for me to by it.
The only complaint I have (this was mentioned in a few other reviews) are the straps. The buttons on them are useless for an adult my size, 5' 7", 150 lbs., I had to adjust the straps but without being able to button them they wouldn't stay in place. For the price I made it work, I just adjusted the straps to my liking and hand sewed 5 stitches on each strap to hold the straps in place. I am now and will be a happy camper.
I recommend this as a perfect traveling/everyday backpack purse. They have a lot of colors to choose from too.
Pic 1: the bag color
Pic 2: where I sewed the straps in place.
My next step is to add all the patches and pins I've collected over the years!!!

Awesome cold weather pants! I bought these because I often have to work outdoors in the cold New England winters for 8-10 hrs at a time. I know these are primarily a ski pant but my work involves minamal aerobic activity. During these times I am generating minimal body heat so insulation is paramount. These pants are definetly a lifesaver. They are warm, waterproof, breathable, go easily over other gear due to the integrated leg gators. Zippered heat vents in thighs help regulate body heat when temp rises or if you go inside briefly. They are almost perfect. I would like to see Columbia design a low activity pant and increase insulation from 100gr to 135-150gr. These would be great for low aerobic winter activity like mine or even hunters / naturalist who maybe in a tree stand for many hours in sub-zero temps in high wind. These pants are expensive but have proved their worth.

I live in an area where mask rates are pathetic... a little over half of the local people are actually wearing the things. Thankfully, South Korea has a giant surplus of this style of mask, and it works as advertised - better than a simple homemade mask or one of those ubiquitous flu masks. They're certainly pricey relative to the flu masks, but compared to the cost of getting the 'rona, or finding out the hard way you were a silent carrier and gave it -to- someone, they're worth every penny. Hopefully our country will start manufacturing them so we don't have to pay to have them shipped across an ocean, but unless that happens, this is probably our best bet for high-quality masks that don't interfere with medical professionals (there STILL aren't enough N95s to go around).

I love these! I‚Äôm the type of person that has to wear a belt because i can‚Äôt stand for my pants to sag or to be tugging them up every time I sit and stand.

I love that these are flat so even wearing a fitted shirt, there‚Äôs no belt bulge.

While I am not the kind of guy who needs designer labels on my clothing, I do like to feel like I am in style. I am always looking for inexpensive alternatives to brand names that do not fall short on style. Belts are not always noticeable and can often blend in to one's outfit. A great belt however stands out just enough that it adds to the outfit without becoming the focal point and thus becoming to flashy. I believe that I am fortunate to have found this product as it is trendy, inexpensive, and not too ostentatious.

The belt came delivered to my door in 2 days via my Amazon Prime account. It was nicely packaged in a sturdy box, then wrapped in a nice canvas bag. Inside the bag the belt was wrapped in plastic and packaged with a very nice tool for adding additional holes to the belt for more precise fitting. The belt is leather with a synthetic pattern on top of it. The buckle has a single prong that fits into the pre-existing holes. In terms of size it was a good fit, and I have not needed to make any extra holes. It fit easily through the belt loops on my pants, and the belt itself fit nicely through its own belt loop. Sometimes belts especially the wider variety have trouble fitting in some pants. This is not the case with this product. I have already received multiple comments on the belt and few people have asked me where I purchased it from. I am happy to recommend this product to anyone looking for a new accessory to increase their fashion quotient.

The one thing that struck me first about this headband was the !00% satisfaction guarantee that the company offered. It makes me feel as if I am making a risk free purchase. With that said, I really like this headband. It is certainly made of quality material that is both breathable and very absorbent but not too thick or bulky for winter or summer use. The elasticity is wonderful because it won‚Äôt easily lose shape and still give you the stretch you need if you have a larger head (like mine) but it has the elasticity to fit small heads securely as well.

This is a great camping accessory for holding your hair and not allowing the sweat of the day to drip in your face. The width is perfect and is hard to find with most headbands on the market. I picked up this Flores Underwire Bra in the black lace, it is quite lovely and it feels like a quality piece. It is not just for show, it offers great coverage and support. There is no push-up padding in the cups, but the cups are fully lined and offer good shaping and it conceals well. The shoulder straps are 1/2 inch wide and the back band is generous in size, it holds you in and does not get lost in your back fat thanks to the boning in the side (this is an old-fashioned term, but I am referring to the supports that are stitched into the sides of this bra).  Overall, I feel ""locked and loaded"" when wearing it, like everything is tied down tight! The straps stay up on my shoulder, I'm not constantly pulling or shifting or itching anything. The smooth cups have a flower pattern to them, but it gives you a smooth line and is not visible under clothing, even under a silk blouse. The label says hand wash and line dry, which is typically recommended for molded cup bras and just helps the maintain their shape. Overall, this bra fits well, offers good coverage and support, it's pretty and reasonably priced! What more could you ask for?! For reference I am 5'4"", 150lbs wearing my usual size 36b.

I like these gloves, but it's a little bit hard to use to use my phone with them. The reason is, even though they fit, they extend past the tip of my finger and thumb. This is because the extra fabric left after it was sewn holds it away from my fingertips. This causes my finger and thumb not to have contact with the touchscreen all of the time (I've had other touchscreen gloves, and this seems to be an issue with those too). If I pull on the glove quite hard and make it tighter, it'll work better, although sometimes not. So far, I've had no problems with them keeping my hands warm, and the temperature has gotten down into the lower 20's, with pretty high winds. I also have a condition that if my hands get chilled, they will react as though they're frost bitten. So far, so good with that characteristic of the gloves. The last important thing is, check the measurements that are given on one of the pictures that are shown at the top their page and do measure your own hands. I normally wear a large and according to those measurements it shows that an extra-large would fit me (if this helps, I wear a medium in medical gloves...or a size 7-1/2 if they're sterile gloves). I went ahead and ordered the extra-large and they fit perfectly.
I'm going to try and trim down the ends of the forefinger and thumb where the extra fabric is. I'll update then if that makes a difference.
Update: I was not able to trim the end of the fingertips because the way they are sewn makes it impossible to do (the interior of the gloves aren't accessible because of the lining). I'll still repurchase once I need new ones.

Although in my opinion, not the best in the X-MEN franchise, I did enjoy the movie. Set in 1983, we find the younger cast of the X-Men movies coming into contact with an older mutant from the age of the pyramids. The humans of that era seem to worship him like that of a god.
Well, for some of them, he was not a god and try to assassinate him while in the midst of a "transfer" of power to a younger body.
We then move forward to current 1983 where we see Professor X and the younger cast of X-Men doing there thing at Xavier's school for the gifted.
I am not a comic book fanatic or reader of the X-Men comics, but I would have thought the four horseman could have been better selected and not well known.
One indication would have been who were the "horsemen" he used before? We saw a scene with him moving the stones into pyramids at the end of the credits in "Days of Future Past". I'm sure they died off in some form, however.
The mutant is awoke by digging humans and his tomb comes into contact with the Sun. He wanders around the city and seeks out other mutants to aide in his "recovery" to a higher power for himself.
It's only a matter of time before the younger X-Men learn of his return and must confront him and his powers.
I really liked Mystique here and Quicksilver, but I wished there were more scenes of Mystique. Magneto has a good time being him, of course, tricked into becoming "Apocalypse's" pawn.
After a brief encounter by Mystique and Quicksilver, Magneto realizes he has "family" worth fighting for and a better future with the mutants.

These are very nice quality polarized sunglasses and I do recommend them.

The come with a thin wooden storage box, a drawstring storage pouch, a cleaning cloth, and a little card that you can use to test that they are polarized. The earpieces do seem like they are real wood. I got the sunglasses with black lenses and am very glad that I did‚Äîthey are a nice level of darkness to block the sun‚Äôs glare, and the polarized effect of them is very good to also block the sun‚Äôs glare.

I have a relatively small face and these fit me well, both in the width across the front of the face and the physical size of the lenses. They do not slip off my nose or face when I lean forward. The right earpiece is completely plain(wood), and the left earpiece has the name of the company and the company logo very lightly engraved into the wood at the temple. It‚Äôs not very dark or obvious though. That may be important to those who either like obvious company brand/logos on their sunglasses, or who prefer plain.

At this time, there is no price advertised, so I cannot comment on the value. However, I am very pleased with these sunglasses, they are good quality, and I like them a lot. I will definitely be wearing these.

I have owned every type make and model of tent up to a 10 person and down to a one person. I am a serious hiker, I own five one person tents. This tent is amazing, the fabric the design and the thought that went into this tent is amazing. You cannot beat the weight and the footprint size of this tent. The inside of the tent when the rain flies applied is so comfortable and private and so much more roomy than any other 1 person tent that I own. The thought that went into this tent for Biking and Hiking is just great , built in gear Loft a place to store your jacket or essentials out of your pack, loops on the outside of the rainfly to secure wet things to dry(genius!) and out of the way and still have room to completely spread out in your tent. The size that this tent packs down to is just amazing, it is so light and take so little room in your pack that you will have to buy a pack of smaller cubic inch because you're going to have empty room in your pack now. Really I don't have anything bad to say except buy the footprint or a piece of tyvek for under the tent. No big deal, I do that with every tent I own. It has survived serious rain and serious snow. I live in the high sierras, do yourself a favor don't look at the price and buy the tent. End of story

I have used the same junky carabiner for many years to hold my keys, primarily to make quick removal easy. However, it's easy for rings to fall off accidentally since there is no lock. This keychain solved all of my problems.

No more accidental removal of rings. The lock on this keychain is excellent. It's almost impossible to disengage on accident, and very easy to disengage on purpose.

No more fumbling around in my pocket. The length of this chain allows me to easily hook to a belt loop for easy access.

No more Chinese junk. This is made in Taiwan out of what appears to be much higher quality materials.

Others have mentioned it is easy to end up with an unwieldy glob of keys, but there are easy solutions. Stagger the groups of keys by attaching a secondary ring to the provided ring, remove unused keys, or buy a different large ring that is actually intended to be used for a large number of keys.

My only gripe would be the price. $20 seems pretty steep for a keychain. Nonetheless, I highly recommend this product.

UPDATE 2019-09-12:

I'm still using the same product I purchased years ago and it has held up wonderfully. I still love it and would buy it again.

UPDATE 2021-10-25:

The finish is a little scratched up but no rust and it still works perfectly. I even bought another one for my wife. This is the keychain I recommend to everyone who cares enough to ask.

I had something very much like this 25 years ago in college and it served me well. I like the simplicity and versatility; I would like it even better if it had fewer colorful markings (for wear with dark clothes). The watch lost a star because when I took it swimming in the ocean, and used the timer functions, that evening the watch developed some condensation on the inside, and 2-3 days later it stopped working. Maybe I had a loose seal. I'm going to get the G-Shock (bought one of those in 1990 and it lasted well over a decade of heavy use); if it's too bulky for the office then I'll get this model again.

UPDATE 8/21/2015: I did in fact buy another one some time ago; it's still cheap, very functional, and understated enough that I can wear it to work in an office setting. And maybe I just assumed that it was waterproof last time, but I now notice that it says "Water Resistant" on the back of the watch, so my bad for taking it into the ocean! It would be silly to dock it for not being water proof since in addition to it saying so on the watch, the web page says resistant rather than proof, so I'm changing it from four to five stars.

I feel like a lumberjack in this red and black plaid shirt and was hoping to pick up a warm but cute camping shirt for those chilly nights.

Here‚Äôs a more detailed rundown of the features:
Appearance. This product is as exactly pictured on the product page. I picked up the red and black. There is a peekaboo detail of white polka dots which is a surprising twist on the plaid shirt. It amps up the style factor a bit which is fun.
Fit. I ordered a small. I am 5‚Äô0 l00lbs and this did not fit me at all. It was way too big. The shirt itself was way too long as were the sleeves and the chest area just was too baggy. If this were tailored a little bit more to my body, I would have liked it. I wear a size 0, xs - s in most clothing so if you are anywhere near my size, it seems that this brands tends to run a little big. I‚Äôd say the small is closer to a US size 2-4. If you have a shorter torso you may find this too long. It just didn't do anything for me and I didn't feel cute in it.
Fabrication/Construction. I was impressed with the fabric choice on this. It feels like a true flannel and will definitely keep you warm. The seaming and stitching is high quality and I did not notice any loose threads.
Price point. At 19.99, this if fair and competitively priced.

Overall, this brand tends to run big so I didn‚Äôt love the shirt on me, but on it‚Äôs own merit, it wis a well constructed shirt that is cute with the polka dot detailing.

If you like your rings large-and-in-charge, this handcrafted Indian ring from Praanjal was made for you! If you are petite like my lady, you may have to become creative to wear this piece.

The ring featured an inner portion that looked like a flower or sunburst pattern, while the outer portion of the ring featured simulated pearls and gold beads. The ring came packaged in a small plastic bag and an unadorned outer cardboard box (see photo). The portion that affixed the ring to the finger was a (really cheap-appearing) adjustable metal loop.

The diameter of the ring fell just under the circumference of a Kennedy half-dollar coin. Thus, you needed sizable hands and a love of the unique to wear the ring comfortably. My lady decided to repurpose the ring since it was far too large for her hand. She snipped off the adjustable ring portion, and affixed a pin to the back of the disk portion. Thus, she now had a small, but eyecatching, broach/pin.

As a pin, this design worked much better than it did as a ring. Since a hobbyist could make this ring into something new, I give it a tentative recommendation.

I bought these to wear at Burning Man 2009. I wanted a boot to protect my feet and lower legs from the playa dust that will cake on to them, but that would also breath, and of course look cool. These boots did all that very well, and with the zipper sides, which I didn't realize these had, they were very easy to get on and off. The zipper is black and doesn't stand out at all. The one thing I didn't take into consideration was all of the walking I would be doing and that is the one weak point of these boots. They simply aren't made as all day hikers. Don't get me wrong they are comfortable for casual wear, but they offer virtually no support, they just aren't a walking boot. Other than that I have been happy with them. After getting back from Burning Man, I threw them in the washer and wear them quite a bit. But for my next journey to Black Rock City, I will have to look for something with a thicker sole and better support. I may bring these as back up wear.

I put this on a 3081.BO which is a polymer cased timepiece.  I understand for good reason it's not recommended to put the poly case pieces on NATO or RAF type straps - Luckily, this isn't a typical strap -- It's a "hard" nylon, low-stretch strap for sure -- But the mount is a relatively stiff elastic - which was surprisingly easy to mount, even with no tools (although I have quite a decent selection of horological accompaniments).  AND HERE'S WHAT HAPPENED -- Was working while a reasonably heavy piece of wood came down against my arm, hitting my watch.  (A) Would've hurt a lot and (B) would've easily destroyed the watch (even if it was steel, I'm sure there would've been damage).  But with the pins going through those elastic mounts, one of them gave its life to save the watch.  Actually found the pin - basically a 90-degree "L" on the ground.  No damage to the strap, no damage to the watch.  Other pin held fine so no watch on the ground (one of the big advantages to NATO/RAF-type straps in the first place).  Long story short, I have a feeling that I'd be sending it in for repair at this point if I didn't have it on this strap.

This jeans are seriously everything! I ordered the Girlfriend ultra light and they look very close to what you see advertised. I absolutely love the fit. I‚Äôve paid much more for Eunina jeans and can honestly tell you they are a higher end boutique brand that‚Äôs good quality. These have little stretch to them. So I do suggest that you pay attention to the sellers size chart found up by the photos. For reference I‚Äôm 5‚Äô tall, weigh 133ish and normally wear a size 4 or 7/27. Because girlfriend jeans are meant to fit loose for the most part, I sized down according to the size chart to a size 3. Which is generally my size for my preferred fit in mom jeans or girlfriend and they‚Äôre perfect. I did follow the size chart though. Just pay attention as the others listed by this seller are quite different. I‚Äôll be ordering another pair in the future and by the chart shown I‚Äôll order my regular size for the pair I have my eyes on. I chose to roll these twice and they hit just above my ankle. The waist hits just about at my belly button. While a straight fit throughout my legs, by sizing down I was able to achieve a fairly snug fit through my waist and bottom. Love the look of these, the wash is perfect with the distressing and the holes line up as they should. As with most of my overly distressed jeans I will wash on delicate cold cycle and hang dry. Putting them in the dryer once dry only to soften and relax them a bit.

Overall I highly recommend these. The seller shipped promptly and they arrived wrapped appropriately. I hope my review has helped someone. Not just a little tacky, but actually sticky enough that when I put my hand into the purse to feel the bottom, it stuck to my sweatshirt and followed my wrist until I unstuck myself. I also noticed a distinct chemical smell-- probably if I cared to keep the purse, I could air it out on a windowsill for a few days-- just something to note.

Also, and equally annoying with the stickiness... the belt around the purse. It actually has a function, not just decoration. The ""buckle"" piece will slide (with great difficulty) along the belt, which tightens or loosens the amount of play all the way around the bag. This means that when you get the purse and open the box (nicely packaged by the way-- dust bag, tissue paper, even a roll of foam to keep the crease where the bag is folded in the box to a minimum).... you will see that the buckle is towards the side of the purse, not centered as it is in the photo. This keeps the belt taut around the bag and so it definitely restricts how wide open the top of the bag will open. SO, I thought, I'll just loosen up the belt a bit, I'll move the buckle to the center front and that will also allow me to open the bag ""mouth"" and fit a wallet, checkbook, etc in there without having to slide my skin/clothing against the sticky Venus fly trap edges. UGHH nooooooo, because moving the buckle is a major pain, and once you have the buckle centered, the belt sags horrifically, because I think I mentioned, this is actually fairly heavy material, so you will end up with the buckle facing the floor, hanging even with the bottom edge of the bag, and it just looks awful. And because the ends of the belt are stitched to the back of the purse, so it's not even a complete circle of belt all around, you can't adjust or play with it to center the buckle but keep the belt taut. All in all it's just a nice try to imitate the original designer's bag, but fail on execution.

(I actually bought the black bag, not the red as stated above).
I have only used this bag twice, but so far, I really, really like it! OK...I really, really love it! It's three interior pockets are deep, which is an unexpected surprise. I never would have thought of this feature as beneficial, but it is. I can put my long credit card-holding wallet in the front pocket vertically, with plenty of room to spare. I use the back pocket to hold my kindle or an agenda/calendar/logbook that fits it perfectly. The center pocket is perfect for my two sets of keys so I always know right where they are...no more endlessly searching for them, finally! LOVE that. You can fit more stuff in if you are so inclined. Personally, I like the slim, stream-lined look. It looks very slim from the side when empty, but once you put a few things in it fills out very nicely.
BEST OF ALL, this cross-body bag is absolutely adorable! It's even better in person than as pictured. What a find at this price! I was torn as to what color to get...now I want more! LOL. I'll be buying at least one more to give to my daughter for her birthday, in a different color, (which I will then be borrowing, a lot!) I showed her the bag, and she was very impressed as well. (She's 26, I'm coming up on 60, so this is a bag for all ages.)
I have to add that I have searched online and in-store at some of the major shopping malls and have found absolutely nothing that appeals to me at all like this one did.
One more thing to mention is that although some have expressed dismay that the two front zippered pockets are decorative only and not actual pockets; I think this bag was designed that way intentionally, because to fill those pockets would detract from the overall slim, streamlined look. I prefer it that way and if you get this bag, you' will see what I mean. It's not a bag to carry everything you would normally stuff into a larger, wider bag, but more of an "essentials-only" type. (Will add photos soon.)
If any problems should arise, I will update this review, but for now, thumbs up and five stars!
UPDATE: The lining inside behind the back pocket ripped out after around 3 months. :( It's very thin material which isn't noticeable until after it rips.

I would love to give this box a better review but I have two serious problems with it. I have a watch box nearly identical to it that I purchased for a third of the price and it had a ten spot compartment. It doesn't use a lock but a double pin latch. It worked great for ten years but I outgrew it. This box uses a lock that began to have issues after only four relocks. I wear a US 22/2X. Though Amazon recommended: ""Based on purchases by customers who wear your size, XX-Large will fit you best."", the seller's size chart in the product description indicated that a US 22 should order a 3X & it: ""allows for a pleasantly roomy fit for added comfort"". This statement combined with the pictures showing a loose fit garment (what I want in a nightgown) led me to order the 3X-Large. When it arrived, the tag said 3X. This fit like a 1X/US 16-18. Not only is it body hugging (body con fit), but the sleeves are too tight, cutting into my arms to the point of cutting off circulation.
I really wanted to like this gown.
The color is great & there are a number of other color options as well.
The fabric feels nice, a terrific t-shirt feeling fabric.

I COULD order the largest, 4X, size, but I do not believe in rewarding bad behavior. It is bad enough that they do not size their garments accurately, but (I thought when placing the order) at least they let you know up front. HAH! Since even their already inaccurate size chart is, itself, inaccurate (making it doubly inaccurate), I do not want to reward this bad sizing behavior by giving them money, even if ordering the 4X would correctly fit my 2X body. I would rather give my hard earned money to a different seller who gives accurate sizing.
I do not recommend.

I can see how some folks may think this little "wallet" is cool, but those people obviously carry very small wallets and like to jump on "coolness" bandwagons.  It is a stretch to even call this a wallet.  There are many true wallets available that have the capability to attach it to your belt or to whatever you wish to attach.  After getting it I certainly don't consider it a wallet.  It is a leather and metal toy-wallet.  It is very much a "minimalist" wallet because it has only minimal usefulness.  I also thought it was cool ... until I got it and realized the coolness was destroyed by its impracticality.  It is WAY too small to be of practical value and much less efficient when you need to get to the stuff that could be more easily and practically carried in a normal trifold wallet.  After going through the hassle of breaking it in per the instructions via the warm water method and sorting through which plastic cards and items I would have to do without (because it can't realistically hold them all), I used it for a couple of days then gladly returned to my trifold.  One really BAD issue is that when you break the wallet in with a certain number of cards - let's say 8 - you will have difficulties if you then wish to carry less because they will not be tightly held within the wallet.  Even the instructions warn of this; therefore, anyone rebuking that fact is contradicting what the manufacturer themselves say!  You can possibly carry more cards than you broke it in with, but not less.  If you don't carry much in your wallet, want something cool and feel the need to brag about what is actually a stupid "wallet" concept, and are willing to endure a bit more effort to get to what is in your wallet, then go ahead and buy it.  But if you carry more than a few credit cards, want to be able to show or see you licenses without having to dig them out of the stack of plastic, and want to carry more than just a few items, this is NOT the wallet you should buy.  Instead, get a good trifold or tablet style wallet.  It is also way overpriced.  When and if Trayvax makes a true wallet I may reconsider and buy from them.

Bought the 6 wheeled version for my daughter in middle school to help lug her school stuff around due to a broken arm. It has helped tremendously getting from class to class. She has been using this for a month now but there are a few things to know....
What I like about it:
1. Holds (4) - 2‚Äù 3 ring binders, 4-5 thin folders, and 1-2 spiral notebooks.
2. The 6 wheeled version looks like a figet spinner (That is from my daughter.. lol).
3. Large side pockets on both sides of the backpack that fit her iPhone 5, lots of pens and pencils, and a 8oz. water bottle.
4. Large deep front pocket....she doesn‚Äôt use this one for school materials, only for her small makeup bag which is super light...(read dislikes).
5. Book bag material is good - seems sturdy.
What I don‚Äôt like about it:
1. The 6 wheeled version does not climb stairs that are of normal height (bus stairs or school stairways). It can only climb the height of a small curb or entrance to house i.e. very small ledge. If it‚Äôs packed full it‚Äôs pretty heavy to pick up by the handle on the book bag!
2. If anything of moderate weight is filled up in the front pocket it will fall over face down on the floor. Will not stand upright!
3. The separate rolling platform ....the underneath portion has the be continuously ‚Äúsnapped back into place‚Äù. If the pieces have snapped loose the book bag will not sit upright and will fall face down. I know that eventually this will break and I will need to rig this piece back together :( And she is not able to snap it back into place with her arm broken!
4. The telescopic metal handle has to be secured with screws and the ones supplied were the tiniest screws ever. She found this out on the 2nd day when the metal handle came unscrewed during her change of class in first period, so the rest of the day she had to have someone carry the book bag from the handle on the top of the book bag (not the metal handle) to every class! Luckily, I am a DIY‚Äôer and found the solution to drill much larger screws into the handle. Problem Solved...handle hasn‚Äôt budged since!! Also, for obvious reasons carrying it from the metal handle will loosen the larger screws over time.
5. The platform should be designed better and weighted more in the front with better feet nobs...AGAIN... the book bag continues to fall face down if the contents inside are not properly organized with the heavier items near the back and the light items in the front. And REALLY what student is gonna take the time to do that?? Not mine!!
6. The buckles that snap the bag onto the platform are starting to become loose. If they break I think it would be difficult to rig that back into place?!?
So, for a few months of her being in a cast it‚Äôs a better solution than the book bag you can only carry on the back. But the wheeled platform portion of the book bag will not withstand a full year of school. Although, she could use the book bag without the wheeled platform once she is out of the cast.

I'm the type of person that researches things, checks out you tube and ""original"" claims which really may not be the best quality. This is a well-made bifold wallet. The leather looks, feels and smells the way it should.

Things I like: It holds all my credit cards, licenses, membership cards, etc. The clear plastic ID window is two-sided, one side for my driver's license the other for the credit card I use the most. (The separate window prevents tap-to-pay devices from reading the wrong card, which has happened more than once when cards are too close together.) The cloth lining makes it easy to slide out cards when I need them.

Things I don't like: Like most wallets with flip-out ID windows, it isn't particularly thin. Of course, that is largely due to the fact that I carry around too many cards.

Things I don't know: I don't know how long this wallet will last. I'll update my review if there are any durability issues.

Love the concept...in fact, this had me shopping for ""normal"" sunglasses again in hopes that I could turn any of them into bifocals. However, the dream is over. One of the stick-on lenses isn't conforming to the sunglasses lens, which as you can see in the picture, creates a very annoying zone in my field of view. I tried a few things to resolve this:

1) removed both of the stick-on lenses, and then re-applied without the water. This worked pretty well, actually...until one of them fell off.
2) warm and cold water - i tried various temps of water...no dice. The same 'gap' would appear.
3) switched lenses - I swapped left for right...nope, same problem. The same stick on lens wouldn't conform.
4) other glasses - I tried them on other glasses, thinking it could just be an issue with these sunglasses...nope. same problem.

Ultimately, my guess is that I got a bad pair...which is unfortunate...but it also could say something about the quality of materials or the ahesive method itself (putting a drop of water between lenses, then drying the excess water).

I suppose I'm back to hunting for bifocal sunglasses...which do exist, and are quite good...they just tend to have limited style options and a really good pair can cost you.

I REALLY wanted to like these, and I rarely leave truly negative feedback.  I live on the beach and wear flip-flops 95% of the time.  Out of the package, they look fine.  But once I put them on, they were just odd.  I always wear a men's size 10 in flip-flops... I never even have to try them on while buying anymore, they just always fit.  These seem to have the toe-strap placed too far back.  This means that my foot hangs over the back edge, while I have an extra 1-1/2"" of ""shoe"" sticking out front.  I can force my foot in forward a little more.  This makes the top strap too tight, and after a few minutes, the shoe still slides forward again on its own.  Yes, there are nice features as described, such as an inset heel and raised arch, but this does little good if you can't keep your foot in the right position.  They are neither soft nor comfortable.  They are just extra thick rubber flip-flops... hardly worth the price.  If they were more comfortable, I might have considered ordering a larger size, but then they would look like thick skis because I'd probably have even more ""shoe"" sticking out in front.  I was so excited to get them that I threw the packaging away in the mail room.  Dumb on my part.  If I kept the packaging, I'd undoubtably return them.

Overall decent skirt.

Pros:
-Long (I'm just over 5'8 and it goes to the tops of my feet).
-Skirt is actually a light ivory color as described (just a notch off of pure white).

Cons:
-The way the under-layer (a layer underneath is sewn in and serves as an underskirt, or like a 3/4-slip, so that your undergarments aren't on full display through the fairly thin material of the skirt) makes the skirt's waistline just a little bit poofy, so those who are weight-conscious might take issue with that. Also, the sewn-in under layer is about three-quarter-length (mid-calve) and in my opinion is a bit too narrow (as in, you can't walk with a long stride in it, even though the skirt itself is full and would allow plenty of room if by itself). In any bright light, it is clear that you have on a much-shorter length slip or underskirt underneath, and I just think that looks a little tacky under a long skirt that hits your ankles (but that may be a personal taste thing).

While I took two stars entirely based on length and constriction issues with the underskirt, I personally plan to solve these issues by turning the item inside out and (very carefully) cutting the underskirt out of the skirt. I will use my own full-length slip underneath instead. I'm willing to modify it in this way because a full-length ivory skirt (that doesn't look such a way as to restrict it to formal evening events) is tough to find, but I understand not everyone will be willing to take a pair of scissors to the underskirt. :-)

First, we received a dress that was significantly different from the picture. We believed it to be a wrong item and simply exchanged it. Second, we received an item that was similar but not identical to the dress in the picture. The solid under-layer of this two-layer dress is cut differently from the photos. The bust line is straight across and really rather unflattering. The photos show a subtle v-neck and also a form fitting contour. This dress is a straight sheath dress, with a straight-line bust, from armpit to armpit, which isn't attractive. The outer lace-layer is lovely, very soft and silky, and it has wonderful drape, but, that bust line is just not attractive. On a fuller figured woman, it looks a bit cheap and unfinished, like they ran out of fabric. On a smaller-chested woman, it looks unflattering because it falls too low. Overall, this could be salvaged, with some creative sewing, but you'd have to know how to sew. I can't recommend this to anyone who can't sew, in order to tailor the bodice properly. Good luck finding what will work for you. This is a three star dress, because to get it to look good, you have to be able to tailor it.

These gowns are very very soft, and long enough to cover me well without being tight on my belly. Another advantage is that they do not ride up on me, because I have a large rear. This makes me very comfortable. Especially on days when I am in lots of pain, I don't want to worry about my night gown not fitting properly, or making me sweat.

They are each a different pattern. Each pattern is quite exquisite. They would cost a bit more, $14.99 each if I bought them separately.

I also like the fact that they are sewn well , and no loose threads like some of the other gowns that I have had in the past. I am sure these will hold up for a while.

I love the fact that these are wash and wear. I can throw them in the washer and dryer, and never have to iron them, EVER! Yeah! All of my clothes are wash and wear. I am way too sick to iron.

BUREI Women‚Äôs 13002-LH Watch

I should begin by saying that I received this product at a discount for a review. I agree with other reviewers as to the presentation of the watch. Once you get the package, you feel like you purchased a very fancy watch ‚Äì which is true. The package comes with an elegant gift bag, the watch encased in a suede pillow, owner‚Äôs manual, warranty card, and a free gift (in my case, I got a fancy hair clamp). I rate them highly on presenting the watch in a very nice way. However, since we are not here to talk about the packaging, let me focus on the main attraction ‚Äì the watch.

The watch is beautiful ‚Äì especially the rose-gold watches. I love watches, and this won my heart. It has a standard adjustment dial on the side of the watch to set the time. According to the manual, the watch is a 30M which means that it has some level of water-resistance to it, but that doesn‚Äôt mean that you would necessarily want to go scuba diving with it. I love the red and blue nylon strap; it looks like you can easily clean they should they begin to look dirty.

If they could change one thing, I‚Äôd suggest they elongate the strap a bit. I have larger wrists, and this watch fit just OK, but it didn‚Äôt leave a little wiggle room to rotate freely around my cuff. Nonetheless, I will keep wearing this watch.

All in all, this is a lovely, decent watch and ‚Äãhas a lot of value in it. I recommend this piece to anyone, especially if you like what you see.

3) Be very careful when you wash them the first time - they bleed dark blue like crazy. We washed them on the cold water setting, with a non-bleach detergent, but they bled on other clothes - badly. I'm hoping subsequent washes won't be a problem, but for at least the first wash - be careful!

Yes, there are TWO bags‚Äî a well-designed medium hand-bag that could be a tote, and a smaller, matching clutch with a cross-body strap. The big bag is sturdy, with excellent handles.

UNFORTUNATELY I couldn‚Äôt use them for over a week. Even from two rooms away, they smelled like jet fuel. I know these synthetic materials are made from petroleum, but they should be allowed to out-gas before they are sold to unsuspecting consumers. I had to hang the bags on the back porch.

I liked the design and size of these bags enough that I was willing to keep them, and even buy more, if it‚Äôs possible to speed up the out-gassing. I asked recent buyers how they got rid of the smell, but they didn‚Äôt have the same experience (although many other customers returned the bags because of the odor).

UPDATE: I didn‚Äôt try washing them in the machine, baking soda, or vinegar. But I DID try activated charcoal, tea, and perfume sachets, and Febreeze. In the end, I got rid of most of the smell just by waiting long enough! I left the bags outside on my back porch in the sun and wind for 8 or 9 days. Then I washed the outside with a damp towel and baby shampoo. I was able to use them today. After handlng the bags, my hands smelled a little bit like jet fuel (from the handles), but it washed off.

Now that they are usable, I raised my review to four stars. After all, I plan to buy them again in another color. But I shouldn‚Äôt have to wash and deodorize them before using them, so I‚Äôm leaving one star off.

I really wanted to like the Republic Chrono Aviation watch. It's very handsome in person, but the quality of the construction just doesn't match the price. Two big problems:

1. On mine, the second hand was misaligned. It does not point straight up at the top of the minute and does not properly point to any of the second hash marks on the dial.

2. The chrono start/stop/reset buttons have a very cheap movement to them that takes more force than it should, doesn't always register a click, and feels like it could break at any moment.

When I spend $100 on a watch, I know I'm not getting a Rolex. Nevertheless, everything should at least align properly, and the controls should give you confidence that the watch will last for many years to come.

Received free to review. The watch itself is beautiful, no problems. I took one star off for the difficulty of removing extra links. Watch came with no instructions, for adjusting time or for removing links. Adjusting time isn't a problem, but how to remove the links isn't exactly common knowledge. I found out that it doesn't matter which side you push the pins out of because the pins are the same both sides. Further more, you need the right size pin to pound the pins out of the links, and you having to be careful with the hammer so as not to break the wood, as my husband did. We glued the broken piece back on.
I feel that the seller should include a small pin (the cost would be minimal) as well as good instructions on how to remove the extra links. I just happened to find a small pin in my junk drawer that happened to do the job, but somebody else might not be so lucky. My teen son was originally very interested in the watch, but the frustration of not knowing how to remove the links made him lose interest in the watch altogether. Or, you can do as another reviewer recommends and ask a jeweler to do it for you. But really, it's not hard to do if you just have the right sized pin, you can quickly tap the connecting pin out with a hammer.

I purchased these shirts for my disabled husband after ordering the women's shirt for myself. He is very sensitive to temperature following a stroke, with a lot of pain in his left arm  if it gets cold, but is also unable to tolerate being too hot. He also continues to have some swelling in his affected arm, so the compression seemed like a helpful feature. I was concerned that it might be difficult to get the shirt on and off as his left side is paralyzed, but the shirt is nice and stretchy so we are able to dress and undress him without difficulty. The shirt is great to wear around the house during cooler weather [we keep our house quite cool in the winter] without being too hot for him to be comfortable. He also loves the nice long sleeves, as many shirts that fit him otherwise have sleeves that are too short. I love the color selections, and got the black, bright blue and charcoal grey for the variety. He and I are both very happy with this purchase!!

**Update: 6/2/22**

So, it appears my enthusiasm for these lower cost winders was a bit premature and I have reduced my rating to three stars. While this unit still adequately functions for my needs, the individual turntable rotational speed tends to be inconsistent if only one heavier weight watch is mounted on a turntable. The turntable gives the appearance of being out of balance and struggles to complete a rotation. I placed a diver style watch weighing around 160 g on the left turntable and it immediately looked like it was trying to drag a boulder up a hill. Once I placed another similarly weighted watch in the second slot, it was fine but the fact it has to be balanced is a concern as there will be instances where I actually wear one of the watches...

**End of update.**

Original review:

As a watch enthusiast and also a vine program participant with an embarrassing lack of impulse control, I've added a number of low end automatic watches to my collection, to the point the number of automatics in my possession far exceeded available slots on the watch winders I owned. In the main, most of these angled carousel winders had too many deficiencies to meet my requirements, let alone meet the TPD specifications of some higher tier watch makers. Notwithstanding those considerations, the Flint 4 slot winders may well be as good as one is likely to find with more economical units.

I consider the Flint 4 slot winders to be of quality construction and above average performance for the price point. While it has a few deficiencies often found with these lower end winders, based on my experience with them (I liked the first one enough to acquire a second four slotter) thus far I don't think many competitive 4 slot units in the sub $200 range are going to equal or surpass it, either in terms of build quality, versatility of mode options, quiet operation or durability. According promotional information, it is driven by two Mabuchi motors, a widely respected driving source found in a healthy proportion of lower to mid-priced watch winders. As is common with that motor, this device is commendably quiet and smooth in operation. I have the same motor in a couple of other winders and it has proven highly dependable, accepting I don't have any of them operating 24/7.

It also features a choice of power options, either AC power or battery. For the latter it requires two ""D"" cell batteries, which in my case powered the two Mabuchi motor driven turnstiles for approximately two weeks when set to rotational mode '4.' While not specifically stated with any of the documentation, I do not believe the batteries should be left in place when the winder is on AC power as with other units I have from other distributors/manufacturers it is noted the winder could be damaged by doing so.

The medium density fiberboard constructed box is covered with a black and gray houndstooth patterned shiny finish polymer sheet covering and features of acrylic glass display forward opening top. As noted above it is appreciably quiet in operation and there is a convenient auto stop mechanism when the top is opened. The watch box is lockable and the package includes a skeleton styled key. The back of the winder houses the battery compartment as well as independent activation switches for each of the two watch turntables. The winder also has a unit power switch and another for the background lighting.

The more or less horizontal orientation of the memory foam pillow cushion slots on this model facilitates accommodation of larger cased watches side by side on one turnstile without the cases or crowns of one watch potentially damaging the other. I have included a photo of two larger case models mounted side by side (the displayed watches on left turntable are not automatic but only mounted for demonstration purposes - I don't own any automatics of that immense -around 48mm each - size.) NONE of these lower price watch winder sellers seem to comprehend cycle time isn't the only specification for automatics and many users need more options to determine the optimal settings for their watches. However, grading on the curve this one impresses me as a much better than most at this price point.

These are a bit odd as a toe ring until you try them on.  Typically toe rings don't have raised stones but after trying them on my wife was surprised  at how much she liked them. German silver is basically a nickle/copper/zinc alloy and contains no actual silver so If you have nickle allergies then do be aware these may not work for you (my wife has a nickle allergy but only with her pierced ears and contact with these rings has not caused any issues).  The only other issue is the split band.  It is super easy to adjust (almost too easy) and the edges where the split occurs are on the sharp side so care must be used to not cut yourself. The problem with this mask is the price and misrepresentation compared to what the customer ends up getting.  The title description says cotton mask,  but the mask is actually made from cheap thin polyester.  It does say 100% polyester if you scroll down for the product details,  but the title next to the image says ""Sika deer mask, cotton...."" For $8.99 I was anticipating a quality cotton well made mask. It's the pleated kind of simple construction. Sewing is ok, but it is just a pleated rectangle.  The deer was positioned on mine so his ears are cut off! What's the point of presenting such a cute idea if it is positioned badly. The deer is pink! Looks beige/tan on line. So the overall effect is a goofy cheaply made thing for  almost $9.00 bucks. Deer is so big it looks like a big pink boomerang crossing my face instead of the sweet tasteful effect I was looking for.  It wouldn't be so bad if it was just $3.00 , but please don't waste your money on this overpriced thing. I'd keep it for grub work to protect me from dust, but think I will send it back because I paid too much for it. Got some other truly cotton masks in sets of 5 that average $5.00 each. Very well made, triple fabric and form fitting,  so it makes no sense to pay $8.99 for this one.

I bought this dress for a special event. It arrived quickly. The lace was somewhat fragile and stretchy while the polyester body wasn't the highest quality, but since it was being worn at night and in low light I wasn't too concerned. My main concern was that the dress ran small. I am about 5'2" and 118 lb. and ordered the size medium based on the size chart. The dress has one zipper in the back, running from the neckline toward the floor. However it only unzips 8", making it very difficult to put on. I could not pull the dress over my hips but rather had to pull it very carefully over my head - putting stress on the lace sleeves, primarily the armpit areas where lace seams meet. Ideally I would have stood with my arms straight in the air and it drop down on me. I actually had to mend a portion of the armhole where the lace stretched from the difficulty of putting it on.

That being said, once it was on, it was a very classic, conservative and elegant dress that I felt good and pretty wearing. I even received compliments on the dress during the event.

The photo, price, and name suggest that this is truly a fine item, especially for the stage. In my opinion, it is not. The photo suggests that it drapes well. It might if you are thin and small, but for a full-figured woman to get the effect that is pictured takes more fabric than what it has. That it is called a dance shawl suggests that it works well for performing. The fabric is thick (though light-weight) polyester, which doesn't breathe and is too hot for performing, especially under hot stage lights. The lightness of the fabric also affects the way that it hangs and moves. Though the color is beautiful, just as pictured, I find it impractical, disappointing to the touch, and overpriced.

[[VIDEOID:330c165cc63aff99cdcd9d81d6082b6]] I got these for my 4.5 year old daughter who recently started swim lessons. These are great, I really like them especially way more than the cheap goggles I had bought her at first. The nose bridge is adjustable by snapping in one of three different length little plastic peices, as opposed to other goggles that end up leaving something awkward in between your eyes if you try to shorten it. It was a little difficult for me to get the piece out so I could snap the smaller one in, but I think other than the couple of seconds of frustration, it's a good thing knowing it's not just going to pop out while swimming. The silicone around the eyes and the head strap really are soft.  it's not that sticky kind that pulls hair trying to get it off wich is a plus for little girls with long hair. True to the description these goggles never fogged up or let any water in, which is impressive since the last pair she used she had to keep lliftting them up to let water out. As a mom I'm also very happy about the UV protection, and having a case to keep them in so the lenses don't get scratched up in her swim bag is pretty cool. The case even has air holes so you don't have to worry about mildew and what not if you put them away with a little moisture still on them.  The only problem I had was the marks around her eyes after her 30 minute classes. The instructor said that's totally normal for goggles but my daughter did complain that her eyes hurt after she took them off. Still she never said she didn't want to put them back on, and she continues to use these for 4 lessons now.  Overall I think these are great quality swim goggles.  As a disclaimer I did receive a discount on these goggles for my HONEST review.

Very different little bracelet.

Three separate strands (braided, flat and twisted) are joined by an ingenious slide knot of cords, which end at 2 silver-toned beads. The flat strip of leather is decorated by (in order) 3 bands of black cord, a brass washer, a silver toned bead(which looks like SSSSS), brass washer and another row of black cord. The twisted band may be leather but feels like cord, has 5 beads in different material, a bronze/brass colored dragonfly danglfing from a silver jumpring connected to a bead, finished with 5 more beads. All strands are very nice, rich browns.

I've had it about a week and worn it constantly (showers, dishwashing, regular chores and work). It's held up well - no fraying, no color bleeding and the knot doesn't slip.

It's cute, eyecatching and versatile. A good buy for the $ and it makes me smile.

Like many people, my leisure time is almost always spent in jeans. So I'm very critical and demanding about how comfortable they are primarily, second how they look, obviously and finally the quality of the stitching and the denim composition. I discovered Joe's Jeans and they instantly became my overwhelming favorite despite an eye watering price, at least in my opinion. I bought multiple pairs of one model of dark blue to assure having them for years to come. These Genuine Assembly Skinny fit jeans arrived and I was immediately struck by the weight of the package. they had heft that might indicate a substantial jean. They have ""skinny"" right in the name so I was prepared to snake into them and pronounce them uncomfortable like compression socks. But I didn't. Though the lower legs are slimmer, I'm not sure I'd call them skinny at all. Maybe slim fit is more accurate. Surprisingly, as other reviewers noted as well. the waist area, even though they are my standard 32 inch waist, were actually a little loose. No wearing these without a belt. But once belted the fit is almost perfect for my form. I love the fact that the pockets don't have some obnoxious stitching that screams No Style Taste, though even expensive jeans can go off the deep end with cheapening details and over design. These have clean lines and an efficient cut and look. The stitching is even and secure. Areas are faded, but in a way that makes it look the most convincing of any pair of jeans I've owned that makes it appear this was caused by genuine wear and washing and not some contrived exaggerated design or acid torture process.  Like many jeans today, the length is a standard 34 inches. I wear 32 length, but the extra length allows you to roll them into a cuff if you like. I coincidentally just bought a pair of sueded Chelsea boots, and these jeans were made to be paired with them, including the extra length. I was asked to review these jeans as a preproduction model so no price was listed on the amazon page. My Joe's Jeans retail for almost $200, so if these are anything under $150, I'd say they are a good value since they should last many years of wear, the material is comfortable with just enough stretch, and the fit, while not exactly skinny as advertised, to me is a more user friendly and comfortable ""slim"". Highly recommended! These are more casual and less dressy, serious looking than my deep blue Joe's, but they will get nearly the same workout in my wear rotation.

This is a nice garment - good quality and well-made. For the right person, it might be a good choice. As for me - I'm considering sending it back. The quality is so good that I cannot give it a poor rating of one or two stars. But the problems are significant enough that I cannot give it more than 3 stars.

The actual fit is true to size. I am a size 2x and the XXL fits me perfectly. This surprised me because most of the reviews stated that it runs big and so I expected a looser fit. The length is perfect on my body - I am tall and it hits me at the low-hip, covering up my butt very nicely. But I wonder what will happen when it is washed - if it shrinks a bit, this will not be appropriate for me because it'll be too small. As it is, I can wear this without a problem, but it doesn't have that roomy feel that I was after and if it shrinks in the wash, not sure it'll fit anymore. Not what I expected, and if I wash it, I might not be able to return it.

The thing I do not like is that the material is super-dense and thick and the design is unforgiving, extremely structured and not at all relaxed. There is very little stretch and it has a mind of its own, making me fight for every movement that I make. It is not too small - but simply too overbearing. The result is that instead of me wearing this shirt, THIS SHIRT IS WEARING ME!!! üò≥ People should never have to conform to their clothes. Clothes should ALWAYS CONFORM TO THE PERSON. This doesn't conform to me.

When I put on activewear that is intended for fun and games or sports, I don't want a prim and proper silhouette. I want a relaxed feel that gives me freedom of movement. This shirt is really the opposite of what I expect in a sweatshirt. I believe that casual garments should be comfortable and relaxed - not stiff and confining. They should conform to the body of the wearer and not make you fight for each movement you make.

It is possible that after washing, it will soften up and be a little bit easier to wear, but after I wash it, I'm not sure that it will still be returnable if it doesn‚Äôt get better. So I'm a bit undecided whether to keep it or not. In a lot of ways, it is a great piece of clothing, but the fatal flaws make me suspect that if I end up keeping it, then eventually it will end up at the thrift store. So I'll probably return it and keep looking for exactly the right thing. It is so close to my ideal sweatshirt that I'll probably go ahead and wash it in hopes of it getting soft and pliable. But if it doesn't, I'll be stuck with a garment that I cannot use.

Being a victim of male pattern baldness and not on board with becoming one of the shaved head lookalikes in our currently divided society.  I am always looking to add to my impressive, ever expanding hat collection. I do have certain parameters but I am willing to try new versions and modified styles that come along if presented well enough online to pique my interest and catch my attention. But, I am a self professed hat snob and I will not give a 5 star approval without being completely satisfied with every facet of the cap under scrutiny. This glorious cap, hits all my personal desired standards and I can find no need for improvement. Quality cotton fabric. Well assembled and stitched with attention to detail, no dangling threads needing to be cleaned up. The embroidery work is expertly done and logo presented in the exact understated eye catching fashion that initially aroused my curiosity. The mesh is unique ,and I believe, probably fabricated in house, from the same fine, soft cotton material used in the rest of the hat. It is both comfortable and functional and allows for a clean and smooth transition at the junction of the solid and perforated cloth materials. This is often not a priority from many manufacturers of mesh back ball caps.  It has a true and consistent olive drab pigment through out and all existing thread used for assembly matches or compliments its fine textile admirably. This is a low to midrise profile, structured crown, mesh back hat with quality hook and loop closure construction ( which is an absolute must for me -""NO SNAPBACKS "") which is my style of choice to suite the larger than average head size which I was dealt. Built by a company called Eagle Crest, model #6847 which I have never seen before but will now put on my radar. So I took a chance with a sight unseen product and it really worked out. Hope I could be a benefit to fellow consumers in offering some well needed specific description that is lacking in their ad.

The reviews posted so far look very generic, and don't provide much detail of any kind. Makes me wonder if they even come from real owners. Anyway, I actually do own this bag. I've only used it for one weekend, so I can't comment on long term durability, but these are my observations so far...

This bag is just a little wider side-to-side and a little narrower front-to-back than an Adidas gym bag that I had been using as a weekend travel bag (overall cubic inches comes out about the same). The big difference (other than appearance) is that the KAKA bag has more pockets than most bags this size. The item description and images here provide a good overview of the pockets, so I won't bother to repeat it. I will simply say that this bag kept my things much more organized and accessible than they've been in the past.

Zippers on the bag are all metal. The front pocket looks like a buckle closure, but that's mostly for appearance, and it actually closes with magnets. The stitching throughout the bag looks good, if not necessarily heavy-duty.

As for overall appearance, some people will like it; some will not. My girlfriend says it's ugly. I said it looks like something Theodore Roosevelt might have used (I have the khaki version). I will say that the bag is a little more "frumpy" than what the pictures here show. When empty, it pretty much slumps over. And even when packed, it doesn't quite maintain the boxy shape and straight edges you see in the images.

I'm including a picture (taken from a cheap phone... sorry) to give some sense of the size and it's general shape when packed.

Well made, well fitting thongs for men. The t-strap in the back is the perfect width for comfort, does not bind or "cut" between the legs. The pouch in the front is well designed for support without being uncomfortable, and it compliments your package nicely under jeans, khakis, or without... So far, the bedroom response has been positive, too! I have worn thongs (not every day) for decades, and these are some of the most comfortable (back, pouch, waist-band) that I've worn in a LONG time, even compared to those I've paid $20-30/pr for....

I normally wear 32-33" waist pants, and US-M underwear. These Asian-L (US-M) fit perfectly for me. I am also above avg size, and the pouch is plenty stretchy enough to maintain comfort, even if slightly aroused.

These are a low-waist (hip-hugger) design, so don't be tempted to pull them up high like a boxer... things should be held low and slightly loose, otherwise the bottom seam will dig into you and the t-strap will slowly saw you in half, lol

My only complaint on quality has been one pair (orange/black) has an issue with the outer black piping on the right leg, where the piping did not catch the orange material for about 1.5", so it appears as a "hole". I am sure this defect will also allow the material to tear, but we shall see. I don't want to return the entire batch to get one pair replaced....

I have bought many tapers and plugs through out the years. These are very handy to have trust me! Over the years I've spent a ton of money on individual tapers and to only go through different sizes through the years. These are perfect because you have every size needed except for anything over 00g. I have not needed the rest of them but I figured it would be nice to have a whole set in case I ever wanted to go smaller. Right now I am at 00g but often times I fluctuate lower just to try new things.

These do not come marked at all, nothing on the bag and no paperwork. If you have experience with gauges then you already know what size each are just by looking at them. A quick helpful hint is the lowest is the smallest which is 14g then just eye which ones is slight bigger and go up to 12g and so on. The highest number in this kit is 00g which means that will be the biggest size. You should be able to figure out which is which now. If anyone has any trouble figuring out sizes, you can always check online too.

Some of the others I have bought in the past have plugs with sharp edges not something you want on your ears. You will be quick to learn why! These are fancy like the other ones but they are still equally nice. The black plugs and tapers are shiny and easy to clean. The best part about this kit is it is the perfect start out one for anyone wanting to gauge their ears. You can start out small and grow higher in size. The packaging of these is incredible each plug and taper comes in their own bag and both are put into another bag for safe keeping. These are all in order from size and accordingly. You get 36 pieces - 4 of each size with 8 different sizes. They also have a stainless steel set which I have not tried yet. I personally always go for the standard dark set because they pair well with everything.

Compared to most kits this is a really great deal. One standard plug can run you anywhere from $15-$60 depending on how intricate the details run on them. Plus, handmade ones tend to run a little more on the pricey side. With this one you get 36 pieces for under $20. I wish I had this kit sooner would have saved me money.

I love this necklace set. Perfect length, seems sturdy. Unlike most cheaper necklaces, there is a loop built into the shape of the pendant to attach to the small connector ring which holds it into the chain (look closely at the image). Never a chance of not being able to reattach it if for some reason I need a new chain.

The bronze one is perfect, smoothly welded/pressed, nicely aged, uniform color, chain matches the pendant perfectly.

The silver one, however.... it's uneven, almost lumpy looking, in spots along the triangle (cloak) - not sure how that happened. Parts of the metal at the corners weren't knocked out properly. I fixed that myself with my pocketknife, not a big deal. While on the bronze pendant, the circle (stone) was attached minimally at both sides to the triangle (below the surface of the pendant on both sides), on the silver necklace, it is completely unattached on one side, and overly attached to the point of being visible on the other side. Finally, in the middle of the triangle, the wand is slightly thin at one point; it is not the same on the bronze pendant nor is it accurate. Very odd, but not so glaringly bad as to return it; unless someone gets about two feet away from my chest, they won't notice.

Again, these are both beautiful, and I intend to keep them both, but it seems as if the silver one was made with a different process than the bronze one, and it didn't come out as well.

Overall, very happy. Perfect length, hangs right on my sternum, not in cleavage or on collarbones. Sturdy construction,

THOMAS HELMET: Material is sound, but this isn't something you'd want to wear straight out if the box. Box was almost too small for the helmet, so when I received it, the helmet was misaligned and the visor was starting to pop off where it was glued.

It works, but I wouldn't buy this for anything more than one party.

Also, this helmet is pretty small. I have an average sized head, but even after I corrected the defects, it was still a pain to put on and take off.

GUY MANUEL HELMET: The helmet itself was straight but the amount of glue they used to "try" and put the visor on was disgusting, and the visor wasn't even attached. This looked like a horrible case of just shooting glue all over the place, slapping the visor on, and sending it off. This, as well, will take a weekend to fix. Must say I was very disappointed at first when I received back in Sep'17 but now I am incredibly surprised by the comfort and very satisfied. I specifically purchased to help with plantar fasciitis but when I tried back in Sept. I did not think they were comfortable enough compared to my regular inserts I use for my flat feet. However, I just had a flare up and thought I'd try them again and I'm blown away with the comfort. They provide the exact level of arch support needed to help with the planar fasciitis. They also provide great support for the ball of my feet and heel. With flat feet although I know I should wear arch support but my case is so severe that I cannot tolerate arch supports. I hope to be able to wear every day but not sure if I can tolerate long term but they provide the perfect support during this flare up. I couldn't put any weight on my foot and the Nazaroo inserts allows me to do so. Of course I'm using my knee scooter but I had to walk and stand a good amount when digging out my knee scooter and the inserts made it significantly more comfortable.

Update 1/25/2018, it's been a month later and I'm still loving these inserts. In fact I purchased 2 additional pair last month and wear them every day. 1 pair for my dress shoes, 1 pair for my running shoes, 1 pair in my Clarke slippers big difference!! I will suggest avoiding moving from shoe to shoe as each shoe holds your foot in a different position and if you have callouses on bottom of feet like me, can make inserts uncomfortable over the long term.

This is a nice summer beach shirt and short set. The material is 70% Viscose, 30% Linen. It seems a little stiff now, I'm hoping after a few washings it becomes softer. The material is fairly thick, and it appears to be well put together and durable. The actual color is more grayish, it appears more blue in the ad. I prefer the color shown in the ad over what I received, mine is a bit bland looking. The fit is good if you go with the size you normally get and ignore the size chart in the ad.
